# Maven Modules

## Parent (`maestro-parent`)

- Java 25: `maven.compiler.source` / `target`
- Shared test deps inherited by all modules: JUnit 5, AssertJ, Awaitility, Testcontainers, Logback (test)
- Version properties: `${version.kafka}` for Kafka artifacts
- New modules: add to `<modules>` in parent `pom.xml`

## Module rules

| Module | Layer | Key deps | Plugins |
|--------|-------|----------|---------|
| `maestro-parser` | Code | `antlr4-runtime` only | `antlr4-maven-plugin` |
| `maestro-engine` | Application | `maestro-parser`, Kafka, Jackson 3 | — |
| `maestro-api` | API | `maestro-parser` | — |
| `maestro-operator` | Operator | application + K8s client | — |

- Internal deps: `${project.version}` (e.g. `maestro-parser`)
- Do not add Kafka to `maestro-parser`
- Do not redeclare parent test deps unless module-specific (e.g. `testcontainers-kafka` in engine)
- Package naming: `dev.vepo.maestro.<module>`

## Commands

```bash
mvn verify                           # full build
mvn -pl maestro-parser test          # code layer only
mvn -pl maestro-engine test          # application layer only
mvn -pl maestro-parser generate-sources   # after Stream.g4 changes
```

## Adding a module

1. Create directory with layer-appropriate `pom.xml` (parent = `maestro-parent`)
2. Register in parent `<modules>`
3. Dependencies point **down** the layer stack only
4. Add `AGENTS.md` module row if it is a new deployment layer entry point
